<div class="staff-title pad">
<div id="imageContentcf453728b64a47199717a2c746dc4117">
</div>
<h3 id="member15">Diana Greenfield</h3>
<p><em>Macmillan nurse consultant in late effects and survivorship for teenagers and young adults</em></p>
<p>Dr Diana Greenfield is Macmillan nurse consultant in late effects of cancer treatment and survivorship for teenagers and young adults at Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust. Diana is working to expand and develop our clinical service to provide care for young people after cancer, including those who were treated in both the paediatric and adult settings. </p>
</div>
<div class="staff-info pad">
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="panel staff-details">
<div class="staff-title pad">
<div id="imageContent997fcea59b694181bcefd19d7d88f936">
</div>
<h3 id="member13">Dr Dan Yeomanson</h3>
<p><em>Locum Consultant Paediatric Oncologist with TYA interest</em></p>
<p>Dan is a paediatric oncologist with an interest in TYA issues. He is a member of the CCLG, sits on the TYAC Research and Registration Sub-Committee and is part of the Sheffield Children’s Hospital Young Person’s Working Group. As part of his role as an oncologist Dan has developed a focus on fertility preservation and has undertaken postgraduate training in paediatric palliative care. Dan works predominantly at SCH and continually seeks to build on links with WPH as the TYA service evolves</p>
<p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:Daniel.Yeomanson@sch.nhs.uk">Daniel.Yeomanson@sch.nhs.uk</a></p>
</div>
<div class="staff-info pad">
<h4>Qualifications</h4>
<p>BM BS </p>
</div>
