</div>
<h3 id="member17">Dr N J Morley</h3>
<p><em>Consultant Haematologist</em></p>
<p>After completing his medical training at Cambridge and London, Dr Morley initially worked in London before moving to Sheffield. He took up his post as a Consultant Haematologist at the Royal Hallamshire Hospital in 2007 following his post doing research into Lymphoma. His specialist interests include Lymphoma, ALL and CLL. He is department lead for Teenagers and Young Adults.  He also has an interest in Clinical Trials and chairs the Haemato-Oncology Research Team Meetings as well a being a member of the Low Grade Lymphoma Trials Group.</p>
<p>Outside of work he is involved in his local church and is married with four daughters. He also loves running and surfing.</p>
<p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:Nick.Morley@sth.nhs.uk">Nick.Morley@sth.nhs.uk</a></p>
</div>
<div class="staff-info pad">
<h4>Qualifications</h4>
<p>B.A., M.B.B.S., MRCP, FRCPath.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
